d 'XTBALFRONT': module to trade-off frontier diagnostics and balanced-subsample selection for unbalanced panel data
d
d  xtbalfront examines an unbalanced panel and characterises the
d trade-off between balanced length (number of years) and balanced
d breadth (number of cross-sections) implied by the pattern of
d missing data on a user-supplied variable list. By default it
d produces a panel-structure summary (xtset + xtdescribe), both a
d "best-window" trade-off curve (best obtainable balanced sample at
d each length) and a "recency-anchored" curve (sample held to end
d at the most recent period), together with a presence/absence
d heatmap, a histogram of per-cross-section data availability, an
d internal-gap diagnostic, and the L*N peak (the largest balanced
d sample). When the analyst supplies years() or crosssections(),
d the command additionally produces a Welch t-test comparison of
d the proposed subsample against the discarded cross-sections, an
d overlaid pre/post histogram for each variable showing the
d distributional shift with the percentage change in the mean in
d the note, lists the selected cross-sections, and either creates
d an indicator variable (generate()) or restricts the dataset
d (keep). A dryrun option lets the analyst review the diagnostics
d before committing. The command emphasises analyst flexibility -
d any window length, any anchor, any subset target - and a
d quantitative read on how the chosen subsample differs
d distributionally from the original unbalanced data. 
d
d KW: panel data
d KW: unbalanced panels
d
d Requires: Stata version 16
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260507
d
d Author: Noman Arshed,   Sunway Business School, Sunway University
d Support: email nouman.arshed@@gmail.com
d
f xtbalfront.ado
f xtbalfront.sthlp
